{SECT 0 {PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 256 38 "Binomial Theore
m and Pascal's Triangle" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 15 "( number03.m
ws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "1.
  Use the MAPLE command    " }{TEXT 257 15 "expand(    );  " }{TEXT 
-1 34 "to calculate the expansion of     " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "
6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 63 "    for values n=1..10 .  \+
In each case use the MAPLE command   " }{TEXT 260 12 "coeffs(  ); " }
{TEXT -1 82 "to pick off the coefficients.   For example if n=5 we wou
ld execute the following:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 
"expand((a+b)^5);\ncoeffs(%);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 24 "Do the \+
rest from 1 to 10" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 265 16 "
Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for finding the coeff
icients of the expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"
\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 64 "  for any n.  It is relatively obvious
 that the coefficient of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^k*b^(n-k);" "6#*&)%\"aG%
\"kG\"\"\")%\"bG,&%\"nGF'F&!\"\"F'" }{TEXT -1 123 "  for any value of \+
k from 0 to n is given by the number of ways we can choose k of the a'
s from the n a's in the expansion " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&
,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 
18 0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }{TEXT -1 18 " ), n times .     \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "The number of combinations of n objec
ts choosing k at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 
27 ", is given by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "
6#/%$nCkG*&-%*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F
*F2" }{TEXT -1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 48 "2.  Verify that the MAPLE syntax for computing  " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 6 "  is  " }{TEXT 258 16 "bin
omial(n,k);  " }{TEXT 264 1 "i" }{TEXT -1 41 "n other words, show that
 binomial(n,k) = " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#*&-%*factorialG6
#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F%6#%\"kGF(-F%6#,&F'F(F,!\"\"F(F0" }{TEXT -1 5 " for " 
